    <input type="file" name="image" />
    <input type="submit" value="Upload Image" />
</form>
```

2. Create the PHP script to handle the file upload.

```php
<?php
$target_dir = "uploads/";
$target_file = $target_dir . basename($_FILES["image"]["name"]);

if (move_uploaded_file($_FILES["image"]["tmp_name"], $target_file)) {
    echo "The file " . basename($_FILES["image"]["name"]) . " has been uploaded.";
} else {
    echo "Sorry, there was an error uploading your file.";
}
?>
```

This script will save the uploaded image in the "uploads" directory with the original file name. You can modify the script to handle different file types, resize images, or store them in a database, depending on your requirements.

